President Obama has nominated John Foster, Paul Ward, and Gary M. Gaskins to be U.S. Marshals. Foster is currently a Judicial Security Inspector with the U.S. Marshals Service in West Virginia. Ward is a Senior Special Agent with the U.S. Department of Agriculture's Office of the Inspector General. Gaskins was previously a Captain with the West Virginia State Police. President Obama praised the nominees for their dedication to public safety and their commitment to serving the country as U.S. Marshals.